+### 5. Link Calibre-Web Automated (CWAuto)
+
+CWAuto uses the upstream **Generic OAuth/OIDC** provider (built in since
+upstream commit `44b053b5`, no fork or code change required). The binding is
+configuration only and lives in CWAuto's `app.db`, not in a Compose file.
+
+Keycloak side:
+
+- Client ID `calibre-web-automated`, confidential, realm `homelab`.
+- Redirect URI `https://cwa.hl.maier.wtf/login/keycloak/authorized`.
+- Web origin limited to `https://cwa.hl.maier.wtf`.
+- Scopes `openid profile email`. The client secret is stored in CWAuto's
+  `app.db` and must never be committed or printed.
+
+CWAuto side (in `config/app.db`, `oauthProvider` table):
+
+- A `generic` provider with `oauth_client_id=calibre-web-automated`,
+  `metadata_url=https://auth.hl.maier.wtf/realms/homelab/.well-known/openid-configuration`,
+  `scope=openid profile email`, `login_button=Keycloak`, `active=1`.
+- `settings` row `id=1` has `config_login_type=2` (OAuth enabled) and
+  `config_disable_standard_login=0` (local break-glass login preserved).
+
+Standard local login remains enabled as break-glass. The running container
+currently tracks the upstream `:latest` tag without a pinned digest; pin a
+digest before relying on reproducible recovery.
+
